class="pt-32 pb-24"><article class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6"><div class="mb-8"><a class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-gold-400 hover:text-gold-300" href="/en/sanctuary">← The Sanctuary</a></div><div class="aspect-[16/9] rounded-2xl overflow-hidden mb-12"><img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1520250497591-112f2f40a3f4?w=1600&amp;q=80" alt="Bale Mountain Lodge" class="w-full h-full object-cover"/></div><div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6"><span class="admin-badge-published text-xs">construction</span><span class="text-ink-400 text-sm">Bale Mountains National Park</span></div><h1 class="editorial-heading text-5xl md:text-7xl mb-8">Bale Mountain Lodge</h1><p class="text-2xl font-serif text-ink-200 leading-relaxed mb-12">A high-altitude lodge at the gateway to the Bale Mountains — for the wild at heart.</p><div class="text-lg text-ink-300 font-serif leading-relaxed whitespace-pre-wrap mb-12">Set at 3,400m elevation, Bale Mountain Lodge is positioned for those drawn to one of Africa&#x27;s most biodiverse mountain ecosystems. The lodge is a base for trekking, wildlife viewing (mountain nyala, Ethiopian wolf), and serious stargazing — wrapped in the same warm-luxury design language across all Sanctuary properties.</div><div class="border-t border-ink-800 pt-8"><a class="btn-primary" href="/en/contact">Explore Investment</a></div></article></div><!--$?--><template id="B:1"></template><!--/$--><!--/$--></main><footer class="border-t border-ink-800 mt-32 bg-ink-900/40"><div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 py-20"><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-4 gap-12"><div class="md:col-span-2"><div class="flex items-center gap-2"><div class="relative w-7 h-7 flex-shrink-0"><img alt="Groovethiopia Logo" decoding="async" data-nimg="fill" class="object-contain" style="position:absolute;height:100%;width:100%;left:0;top:0;right:0;bottom:0;color:transparent" sizes="28px" srcSet="/_next/image?url=%2Flogo.png&amp;w=16&amp;q=75 16w, /_next/image?url=%2Flogo.p